result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Criminal Case Settlement

Cases 16CF98, 16CM56, 16TR236 & 16TR237 called together at 10:03 am [Clerk SH]
Defendant Eugene O Trimble in court with Attorney David Kennedy Anderson. ADA Jeffrey Martin Shock appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights given; plea of "Guilty" entered on Count #1-16CF98; factual basis stipulated; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2-16CF98, Cases 16CM56, 16TR236 & 16TR23

On Count #1-16CF98, the Court sentences the Defendant: 
--To serve 8 months in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges; to commence 
forthwith
--Days credit for time already served: 0 days
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process
--To pay fine of $900 + costs, fees, assessments & surcharges + $56.74 blood testing fees = $2253.74; due in $50 increments per month beginning 8/31/16 and on the last day of the month thereafter until paid in full; non-payment will result in 46 days in jail with Huber privileges, consecutive
--Revocation of drivers license for 27 months
--County alcohol/drug assessment ordered
--Victim impact panel attendance
--Ignition Interlock Device requirement/restrictions for:
 27 months
--6 demerit points assessed
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
Defendant may serve in Dane County as long as electronic monitoring is not utilized
Recess: 10:27 am
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 14, 2016 at 09:30 am.
Final status/scheduling conference on July 14, 2016 at 09:30 am.

Cases 16CF98, 16CM56, 16TR236 & 16TR237 called together at 11:12 am [Clerk SH]
Defendant Eugene O Trimble in court with Attorney David Kennedy Anderson. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Anderson informs the Court that they have reached an agreement in all cases, but are asking for future date for plea/sentencing, presents basis. 
ADA Hall informs the Court that the State would have no objection as long as Mr. Trimble is equiped with the SCRAM bracelet
Court presents basis and informs Atty Anderson that It will not adjourn the trial date, and that case must resolve before the assigned trial date. Will put over plea until next week if needed. 
Court reminds Mr. Trimble that his bond/conditions of release remain in effect while the case is pending
Court informs parties that It will leave trial on the calendar and treat the 14th as a rescheduled FSSC in case Mr. Trimble changes his mind about entering a plea
Recess: 11:21 am 

NEXT: (1) ALL CASES: Schedule Plea/Sentencing 7/14/16 at 9:30 am - Send notices
16CF98 & 16CM56: REschedule FSSC 7/14/16 at 9:30 am - Send notices
Scheduling

Final status/scheduling conference on July 5, 2016 at 10:00 am.
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 5, 2016 at 10:00 am.

Reserve Judge Davis presiding for Branch IV:  
[MK] cases #16CM56 & #16CF98 called at 10:21am.  
Defendant Eugene O Trimble appears via videoconferencing from the Dane County Jail, in custody on a Probation Hold there.  His counsel, Attorney David K. Anderson is present in court.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Service of Complaints admitted, reading waived, the charges and maximum penalties are recited
The Court finds probable cause to exist in the Criminal Complaints. 
As to Case #16CM56:  Pleas of "Not Guilty" entered; speedy trial waived by the Defense. 
As to Case #16CF98: Preliminary Hearing time limits waived by both parties.

The Court requires a $5,000 Signature Bond which applies to both cases, with conditions: 
--no acts or threats of violence
--to maintain absolute sobriety: no possession or consumption of alcohol 
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--not to drive a motor vehicle without a valid drivers license 
--this Bond is to be signed by 3/16/16 at 9:40am. 
recess 10:26am. 

NEXT:   (1) Pretrial Conference on 3/16/16 at 9:40am  (2) Status Conference on 5/6/16 at 1:30pm (clerk's note:  Attorney Anderson indicated that it is anticipated that Mr. Trimble will be in Dane County on Huber privileges through the next several months)
